      "shouldTranslate": false,
      "original": "An iron blade forged in the far east, and carried to the Frost Marches by an exiled killer made faceless for her crimes. In her hands this blade took countless lives, all in service to the one man in all the world that gave her a chance despite her checkered past — and who condemned her to become a dervish of corruption in his mad pursuit of power. Like its mistress, the blade broke under the surge of dark magic that consumed her; like her, it was reborn in fire and lightning.\n\n<b>Special Effect</b>: If your Corruption is less than 50, the penalties to Mental and Magical Resistance triple. If your offhand is empty, the weapon's damage increases by +10 Fire and +10 Storm.",
