      "id": "505.0be08e4a11933fd00e3d.js:536265:536969:6717b971b537",
      "file": "505.0be08e4a11933fd00e3d.js",
      "category": "dialogue",
      "shouldTranslate": false,
      "original": "This model of crossbow has been the stuff of legends amongst lupine mercenaries for centuries. Originally adapted from those wielded by Khor'minos' shock troops, the average lupine, lacking a minotaur's raw strength, found the weapon impossible to set barehanded. They thus resorted to using a specialised lever known as a ramsfoot to span its deadly draw, which eventually became part of the crossbow proper.\n\n        Once loosed, the immense, forearm-length bolts reputedly punch through everything — armor, walls, people, trees, palisades, what have you; it's been a point of argument amongst some enthusiasts about whether the mauler can be properly classified as a siege weapon or not.\n        ",
      "translation": "",
      "start": 536265,
      "end": 536969,
